319-    "summary": "nginx ingress prefix-mount WITHOUT rewrite-target makes a HEALTHY app 404 its own routes. agg.dev telemetryfunctiontestsfn 404: ingress path /telemetryfunctiontestsfn/ (pathType Prefix, no rewrite) forwards the unstripped path to an Azure Functions host that serves /healthz at ROOT. siteregistry works ONLY because mounted at '/'. deliveryreportfn 404s identically (systemic). Topology: DNS->App Gateway vpp-agw-d (WAF_v2, Basic pass-through, 20.76.210.221)->AKS nginx v1.14.0 (50.85.91.121, ns vpp-agg)->ClusterIP:8080->pod.",
320-    "root_cause": "AGIC->nginx migration (PR 150758, Nov-2025) switched ingress class to nginx and dropped the appgw annotation, but never added the nginx equivalent. The chart's only prefix-strip was appgw.ingress.kubernetes.io/backend-path-prefix (AGIC), which nginx silently ignores. nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/rewrite-target was never committed (git -S = 0). Legacy migration gap, not a regression. Verified vs live helm release v215 chart 0.1.27 (annotations:{}).",
321:    "fix": "Add to the chart values (Eneco.Vpp.Aggregation/azure-pipeline/Helm/<svc>/values.yaml; mirror in deliveryreportfn): path /<svc>(/|$)(.*) + nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/use-regex:'true' + nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/rewrite-target:/$2 (class already nginx). Proven by composition (backend /healthz=200). Restores /healthz only; the *fn are timer/Kafka-triggered QA test functions (ADR AL006), no HTTP functions (/api/*=404,/admin/*=401). Alternative: use canonical OpenShift agg.dev-mc (Route rewrite already correct) but it is internal-only (needs AVD whitelist, wiki 44740). NOT a fix: image re-sync or AVD whitelist.",
