370:    "summary": "A K8s Secret present in some environments but missing in ONE (pod FailedMount \"secret X not found\") is usually a DEPLOY-PATH ENROLLMENT GAP, not dead code. Different envs can use different deploy paths: MC may deploy a Helm chart via a GitOps app-of-apps + OCI registry, while a sandbox/legacy env uses an in-repo pipeline that omits it. A single repo string-search can FALSE-NEGATIVE (glob push-loops like `for i in $(ls Helm/)` never contain the literal chart path) - verify via CONSUMERS (OCI registry, GitOps repo). Use ownerReferences (NOT managedFields) as the manual-vs-controller discriminator: on K8s 1.31.x even CSI-projected secrets can have empty managedFields. CSI SecretProviderClass secretObjects are projected only while a pod mounts the SPC as a CSI volume (mount-coupled, can orphan when an unrelated mounting pod scales to 0); ESO is mount-independent.",
371:    "root_cause": "Investigations stop at \"where is X defined?\" (grep) instead of \"what deploys X in THIS environment?\". Env-specific deploy paths diverge (GitOps+OCI vs legacy in-repo Helm). managedFields can be empty for controller-projected secrets, making it an invalid provenance signal. CSI projected secrets are a side-effect of an active SPC CSI-volume mount, not standalone objects.",
372:    "fix": "Triage \"secret in env B but missing in env A\": (1) kubectl get secret X -o json -> ownerReferences absent + no helm/csi labels => hand-made; (2) check BOTH deploy paths incl. the GitOps repo + OCI registry, never trust one ado-repo-search; (3) if wiring via CSI, the CONSUMING pods MUST mount the SPC CSI volume or the projection orphans - prefer ESO; (4) NEVER delete a shared chart/template another environment still renders from (verify cross-env consumption first). Full chain: task 2026-06-02-001 RCA.",
