405:    "summary": "Cosmos NormalizedRUConsumption is a per-partition-key-range MAX utilization GAUGE (0-100%, 1-min), NOT a client-impact metric. Confirm throttling with the HTTP-429 RATE = TotalRequests(StatusCode=429) / TotalRequests(all), per Microsoft's 1-5%-healthy / >5%-act framework. Do NOT use the gauge % or the Mongo error-16500 COUNT as the impact figure: 16500 is counted per protocol-op INCLUDING driver retries (up to ~9x), so it is inflated. STAKES-CLAIM: if on-call/RCA acts on the gauge or the 16500 count instead of the 429-rate, they over-provision RU or page on healthy-band noise (or, inversely, dismiss a real >5% throttle). 2026-06-15 gurobi-cosmos: 77.67% RU-avg + 16,555 16500-events implied 'severe ~34.5% throttle', but the true HTTP-429 rate was 586/20792 = 2.82% \u2014 INSIDE Microsoft's 1-5% healthy band. FALSIFIER: a window where 429-rate>5% was treated as noise, or where 16500-count equalled distinct-op failures (no retries) \u2014 either would break the rate-not-count rule. STAKES-CLASS: HIGH.",
406-    "root_cause": "NormalizedRUConsumption = max over partition-key-ranges per minute; a PT15M Average of per-minute maxes can be brief sub-second spikes (confirm with TotalRequestUnits: the 2026-06-15 hot minutes served only ~3292 RU/min ~= 55 RU/s avg). Mongo 16500 counts every rejected protocol op incl. SDK retries, so its count >> distinct throttled ops and >> the backend HTTP-429 count (16,555 vs 586).",
407-    "fix": "Triage a NormalizedRU alert with: az monitor metrics list --metric TotalRequests --filter \"StatusCode eq '429'\" (numerator) over the same metric all-status (denominator) => rate. <=5% + self-resolved = healthy/ack; >5% or sustained = act/escalate. Size autoscale from TotalRequestUnits demand, not the gauge. For spiky workloads, page on 429-rate>5% and demote the RU% gauge to a Sev3 warning.",
