title: "Classification Spine (eneco-sre)"
description: "The shared origin+surface classification spine eneco-sre runs before any probe: taxonomy, confidence rubric, epistemic ledger, and the 4-predicate handover contract."
type: reference
---

# Classification Spine (eneco-sre)

The shared reasoning both routes (Intake R1, Troubleshoot R2/R3) run BEFORE any
probe. Lifted from the four eneco intake/alert skills, which already share this
spine — eneco-sre formalizes the first classifier hop (origin + surface) above it.

## 1. Origin taxonomy (which front door)

| Origin | Signals | Front-door skill (route to) |
|--------|---------|-----------------------------|
| **Slack-Lists** | `slack.com/lists/T*/F*?record_id=Rec*`, raw `Rec…` id, `#myriad-platform` workflow-bot card. Real ticket lives in the **companion-channel thread** (hex suffix ~matches list file id — verify, don't assume). | `eneco-oncall-intake-slack` |
| **Rootly / Azure alert** | Rootly URL / short-id (`rXLWFd`) / UUID / rule name `{service}-{resource}-{condition}-{code}-{env}` (env suffix `-p/-a/-d/-sb` parsed from the NAME). | `eneco-oncall-intake-rootly` → mechanics `eneco-tools-rootly` |
| **Raw report / direct** | a screenshot, an error string, "help me fix X" with no Lists/alert wrapper. | eneco-sre owns end-to-end |

Origin selects the front-door skill and the harvest source; it does NOT change the
surface step. Interrogative "can you ack?" ≠ authorization — only an imperative
"ack rXLWFd" authorizes a write (mood, not verb, is the signal).

## 2. Failure-surface taxonomy (load the kind reference)

Surfaces are the FIRST classifier axis (chosen over service-domain so a bare
"ArgoCD auth error" routes by surface regardless of which VPP service it hit). Each
surface ref names its own near-miss discriminators.

| Surface (ref) | Selector vocabulary | Sibling domain skills |
|---------------|--------------------|------------------------|
| `surface-gitops-argocd` | ArgoCD OutOfSync, app-of-apps, ApplicationSet, source-N auth, PAT expiry, FBE slot | `eneco-fbe-troubleshoot`, `eneco-flex-trade-optimizer` |
| `surface-terraform-iac-apply` | terraform/terragrunt plan/apply/state, ForceNew, `moves.tf`, immutability, var-precedence | `eneco-platform-mc-vpp-infra`, `eneco-flex-trade-optimizer` |
| `surface-azure-resource-alert` | Azure Monitor / Rootly metric: Cosmos 429/latency, SQL CPU/deadlock, SB deadletter/topic-size | `eneco-platform-mc-vpp-infra`, `eneco-tools-rootly` |
| `surface-messaging-servicebus` | topics/subscriptions, DLQ buildup, subscription filter, MassTransit, cross-env drift | `eneco-tradeit-servicebus`, `eneco-flex-trade-optimizer` |
| `surface-openshift-runtime` | acc/prd `oc`, OpenShift, CSI mount, HAProxy route, manual ArgoCD sync, solver/gateway pod | `eneco-flex-trade-optimizer`, `eneco-platform-mc-vpp-infra` |
| `surface-pipeline-ado` | ADO pipeline/build failure, `NU190x`, git error, "review this PR" | `eneco-pull-request-review-ado`, `eneco-fbe-troubleshoot` |
| `surface-identity-credential-expiry` | a cert/secret/PAT/token EXPIRY cascade — AADSTS, Kafka/broker certs, AKS kubelet, shared-SP / storage-key / KV-secret (auth fails with NO deploy/config change) | `eneco-platform-aad`, `eneco-fbe-troubleshoot`, `eneco-flex-trade-optimizer` |

**Cross-surface near-miss** (shared ArgoCD/Terraform/Azure-credential vocabulary):
- a slot name (`afi`…`voltex`) or pipeline `2412/2629` → FBE under `gitops-argocd`, NOT FTO.
- `flextradeoptimizer-*` workloads + Gurobi + `ac-fto`/gRPC port cascade → FTO.
- flat `MC-VPP-Infrastructure` repo / MC alert metric / one-way-door IaC → `terraform-iac-apply` or `azure-resource-alert`, no app-workload symptom.
- disambiguate a bare "ArgoCD auth error" by namespace + ApplicationSet name (FBE `vpp-feature-branch-environments` vs FTO app-of-apps).

## 3. Confidence rubric → output shape (shared across all routes)

| Confidence | Intake output | Slack answer (see slack-answer.template.md) |
|-----------|---------------|----------------------------------------------|
| **100%** | intake + committed conclusion | 2–5 sentences (ping · diagnosis · action · link) |
| **70–99%** | intake + falsifier / handover | 3–7 (confirmed / remains / next step) |
| **40–69%** | intake + name the probe, no fix | 2–4 (taking it + what + when; ack-only OK) |
| **<40%** | intake with `A3` + context-to-fetch | do NOT reply (acknowledge only if filer visibly blocked) |

## 4. Epistemic ledger (the tags — keep skill vocabulary, NOT brain A1/A2/A3)

| Tag | Means | Promotion rule |
|-----|-------|----------------|
| **Known** (A1) | probe cmd+output OR authoritative URL | — |
| **Inferred** (A2) | a named inference chain, not observed | needs a probe to become Known |
| **Assumed** (A3) | taken on faith; names the probe that resolves it | NEVER silently promote to Known |
| **Unknown** | explicit gap | name the probe that COULD resolve it |
| **Refuted** | a probe contradicted it (added during enrich) | — |

**Non-contradiction ≠ confirmation.** A probe that fails to disprove a hypothesis
does NOT confirm it. The intake instances use Known/Inferred/Assumed/Unknown to
stay compatible with the downstream `eneco-oncall-intake-enrich` consumer (brain
A1≈Known, A2≈Inferred, A3≈Assumed if a bridge is needed). Never fabricate an
identifier — mark the field `Unknown`/`A3` and add it to "context to fetch".

## 5. The four-predicate handover contract (the dispatch interface)

An sre-intake.md — and any handoff to enrich / the troubleshoot route — MUST carry
all four. Missing any one = the handover cannot advance.

1. **Identity ledger** — environment, resource ids (slot/build/sub/RG/branch/GUID), resolved, no `<placeholder>`.
2. **Mechanism hypothesis WITH citation** — the inference chain + the authoritative source (MS Learn → vendor docs → Eneco wiki → Slack), tagged Inferred until probed.
3. **Probe candidates with RESOLVED ids** — exact commands (`az devops user show --user 7edd…`, never `<SP-GUID>`) + the expected-if-correct output + the "else → alternative hypothesis".
4. **Human-decision gates** — severity/escalation, above-project-scope grants, prod config change, one-way-door authorization.

## 6. Write gate (default posture)

Read-only by default. Any state-changing action (a fix, an ack, a whitelist
toggle, a sync) requires **explicit current-turn authorization** + a passed
`sre-safety-preflight.sh`. "N/A — <reason>" discipline: keep the heading, never
silently omit a section (silent omission forces a context round-trip).

**Execution-access boundary:** MC dev/acc/prd OpenShift (`oc` / the OpenShift console)
is behind the Azure Virtual Desktop (AVD) — the agent CANNOT run those proofs directly;
hand them to the user or run only with explicit authorization + computer-use
(`mc-avd-execution-boundary.md`). Azure (`az`) access is NOT behind AVD.
