title: "Surface: gitops-argocd"
description: "Failure-surface reference for ArgoCD/GitOps sync faults (FBE and FTO app-of-apps): trigger signals, do-not-collapse probes, safety gates, sibling skills, near-miss."
type: reference
---

# Surface: gitops-argocd

ArgoCD / GitOps sync failures — the layer between a green pipeline and a live URL.
Spans **FBE (Sandbox)** and **FTO (acc/prd app-of-apps, MC/OpenShift)**. Primary siblings:
`eneco-fbe-troubleshoot`, `eneco-flex-trade-optimizer`.

## Access & tools (Sandbox vs MC — who runs what)
- **Sandbox FBE = DIRECT agent access** (NOT AVD). The agent runs `kubectl --context vpp-aks01-d` (Sandbox AKS) AND the **`argocd` CLI** against `argocd.dev.vpp.eneco.com` directly. Login once with `argosandboxlogin`, then use the read-only `argo-sick` / `argo-drift` / `argo-stuck` / `argo-why <app>` / `argo-tree <app>` aliases (see `eneco-clis-and-tools.md`). **Most FBE GitOps troubleshooting happens here and the agent can probe it itself** — start with `argo-sick` / `argo-drift`.
- **MC acc/prd (FTO app-of-apps on OpenShift) = AVD-gated.** `oc`/console access is behind the Azure Virtual Desktop (`mc-avd-execution-boundary.md`) — the agent prepares the commands; the USER executes them (or authorized computer-use). Azure `az` is NOT behind AVD.

## This IS an FBE (Sandbox) incident when…
a fixed slot name (`afi boltz enel ionix ishtar jupiter kidu operations veku voltex`), pipeline `2412`/`2629`, a `*.dev.vpp.eneco.com` URL, "feature branch environment", or an app-of-apps in the `argocd` namespace on Sandbox. **Classify it FBE immediately** and load the vault `fbe-errors/` (rich recipes) — do NOT leave it as a generic "ArgoCD OutOfSync".

**Invert the burden of proof (the generator rule):** on EVERY Sandbox/dev gitops-argocd incident, **DEFAULT to FBE and look for the DISCONFIRMER** — an FBE incident usually arrives described by its GitOps SYMPTOMS (a mixed-branch 404, an app-of-apps `Deleting`/stale, an OutOfSync slot), NOT by the word "FBE"; the human asking is precisely the one who does not yet know it is FBE. Decide FBE-vs-generic BEFORE generic OutOfSync triage, so the rich `fbe-errors/` corpus is the prior, not an afterthought.

## Trigger signals
- ArgoCD `OutOfSync` / `Missing` / `Degraded`; app-of-apps not Synced; mixed target branches across an app and its children.
- app-of-apps badge **`Deleting`** / a stuck or stale (e.g. 23-day-old) last-sync → **STUCK-FINALIZER** (`eneco-vpp-argocd-finalizer-blocks-feature-branch-deployments`): a finalizer blocks the FBE deployment. A DISTINCT FBE failure mode from mixed-branch — vault `fbe-errors/` has the recipe.
- `ApplicationSet` errors; `ComparisonError … source N of M … authentication required`; `ApplicationGenerationFromParamsError`; `repocreds`.
- PAT expiry; `AADSTS700082` (FTO ArgoCD token expired, 90-day inactivity); shared-SP `AADSTS7000215/7000222/70011`.
- FBE: slot name (`afi boltz enel ionix ishtar jupiter kidu operations veku voltex`), pipeline `2412` (create) / `2629` (destroy), URL `404`, empty/`Terminating` namespace, Pester "Total: 4 Success: 1".
- `SecretNotFound` CrashLoopBackOff (per-FBE Key Vault secret).

## Orthogonal probe surfaces (≥3 before naming a class — else label A3)
Pipeline · GitOps/ArgoCD · runtime URL — every diagnosis must cross the
Terraform/Azure ↔ GitOps substrate boundary (M1).

DO-NOT-COLLAPSE:
- **ApplicationSet generator-plane auth (PAT expiry) ≠ Application source-N credential gap** — DIFFERENT FIXES (H-ARGO-2). "source N of M" with a HEALTHY ApplicationSet ⇒ register the missing credential template; do NOT rotate the generator PAT.
- **Green build ≠ runtime health** (H-STAGE-1): pipeline 2412 Stage-5 tolerates child failure and Stage-7 Pester gives false-negatives; a manual `curl` 200 overturns a Pester "1/4" outage claim, and a green build never proves the URL serves.
- Main `vpp-feature-branch-environments` ApplicationSet ≠ `feature-branch-environment-monitoring-stack` — same-timestamp auth fail = shared credential; different timestamp = separate classes (do not flatten).
- Credential-looking failures are NOT one class (H-SECRET-1): ArgoCD-GitOps PAT / runtime shared-SP / source-N repo cred / per-FBE Key Vault secret / Azure identity.

## Probe starters (resolve ids first)
```bash
kubectl --context <ctx> get applications.argoproj.io -n argocd -o wide | rg <slot>
kubectl --context <ctx> describe applicationset vpp-feature-branch-environments -n argocd   # .status.conditions
kubectl --context <ctx> get pods,ingress -n <slot>
curl -sS -o /dev/null -w "%{http_code}\n" "<public-url>"
```

## Safety gates (READ BEFORE acting)
- **HALT — destroy pipeline `2629` is NOT a rollback** (H-DESTROY-1, F19): it pins an OLDER Terraform version and is a known residue source. Requires a human platform-owner to accept residue risk. The auto-eviction Logic App `vpp-fbe-autodelete-trigger` (weekdays 14:30 W.Europe, 4-day-stale) fires 2629 with `bypassEnvironmentOwnerValidation=true` — name this flag when warning.
- **Confirm Sandbox subscription** `7b1ba02e-bac6-4c45-83a0-7f0d3104922e` before any command; never trust the default `az` sub.
- **acc/prd ArgoCD sync is MANUAL** — force-sync needs team approval; auto-sync is sandbox/dev only.
- Tier-1 minimal mutation: ONE targeted sync; do NOT restart `argocd-application-controller` (reads on reconcile); do NOT batch-disable prune/selfHeal. Isolated `KUBECONFIG` per incident.
- **NEVER echo PATs/secrets** into chat/stdout/logs.
- For an **FTO / MC acc/prd** ArgoCD app on OpenShift, `oc`/console access is behind the **AVD** (`mc-avd-execution-boundary.md`) — hand the proof to the user or run only with authorization + computer-use. (FBE Sandbox is AKS `kubectl`, agent-run, NOT AVD.)
- **Retry-safety + effect-witness:** a targeted `argocd app sync` is idempotent; a *partial* sync (some resources errored) is detectable via `argocd app get` and safe to re-run; a `--prune` sync is NOT freely retry-safe — confirm the prune set first. After a sync, the fix is closed only when `argocd app get` = `Synced` AND `Healthy` AND `curl` of the URL = 200 (H-EFFECT-1) — `OperationSucceeded` alone is NOT the effect.

## Sibling skills / tools
`eneco-fbe-troubleshoot` (FBE classifier + `route-fbe-symptom.sh`), `eneco-flex-trade-optimizer` (FTO app-of-apps + `fto-argocd-status.sh`, argo aliases `argo-sick/-drift/-stuck/-why/-tree`), `eneco-ootw-renewpats-argocd` (rotate an expired MC ArgoCD credentials-template PAT), `eneco-context-repos` (source/branch), `eneco-tools-connect-mc-environments` (Sandbox sub).

## Near-miss (route elsewhere)
- slot name or pipeline `2412/2629` present → FBE under THIS surface, NOT FTO.
- `flextradeoptimizer-*` + Gurobi + `ac-fto` App Config + gRPC port cascade → FTO; the gRPC timeout is a config-auth cascade, classify under `openshift-runtime`/`terraform-iac-apply`, not a network problem.
- bare "ArgoCD auth error" → disambiguate by namespace + ApplicationSet name before assigning the sub-class.
- Terraform state/apply failure with no ArgoCD symptom → `surface-terraform-iac-apply`.
