# Surface: terraform-iac-apply

Terraform / Terragrunt plan, apply, state, and the **one-way-door** changes that
can destroy stateful infrastructure. This surface carries the cluster's most
catastrophic gates. Primary siblings: `eneco-platform-mc-vpp-infra`,
`eneco-flex-trade-optimizer`, `eneco-pull-request-review-ado` (DAG review).

## Trigger signals
- `terraform`/`terragrunt` plan/apply/state failures; `ForceNew`; `moves.tf` / `moved{}`; `prevent_destroy`; `immutability_locked`.
- Local plan ≠ CI apply (var-file precedence); `mise.toml` TF version skew (local 1.14.3 vs pipeline 1.13.1).
- FTO: `dependency.outputs in locals`, stale `.terragrunt-cache`, state-key collision, PostgreSQL role (`azure_tenant_id` missing), KV name mismatch `kv-fto-d` vs `kv-fto-dev`.
- Terragrunt `dependency` (singular) vs `dependencies` (plural) — only plural serializes `run-all` (non-deterministic `SubnetNotFound` otherwise).

## Orthogonal probe surfaces (do-not-collapse)
- **"Where do I change X"** (MC, DF1): module INTERNAL behaviour → NOT `MC-VPP-Infrastructure` (bump `?ref=` in `Eneco.Infrastructure`); alert threshold → `{env}-alerts.tfvars` ONLY; core infra → `{env}.tfvars` + root .tf, ALL THREE envs (dev→acc→prd); KV ACL → default-deny superset.
- **"Is this reversible"** (DF2): SQL `immutability_locked` / `moves.tf` blocks / KV `network_acls` / `prevent_destroy` → STOP, classify as a one-way door.
- **PRECEDENCE TRAP**: `just plan` applies `{env}.tfvars → {env}-alerts.tfvars` (alerts win); CI applies the reverse (core wins). A duplicate key ⇒ local plan ≠ CI.
- The declared `kubernetes` provider governs ZERO resources (route K8s tasks OUT to ArgoCD/app repos). Filenames are load-bearing (typos `dasboard.tf`, `metric-alerts-eventhhub.tf` are NOT to be "fixed" — a rename in a flat root = state re-plan/orphan + diff noise).
- FTO infra suffix maps (`kv-fto-dev`, Postgres `d/a/p`) are INDEPENDENT of GitOps overlay suffix usage — only `sb` is identical (Naming Collision Matrix).

## Safety gates (CATASTROPHIC — HALT before any of these)
- **KV / App Configuration name change = ForceNew = destroy + recreate** → loses ALL secrets, RBAC, private endpoints + a **30-day soft-delete purge lockout** (multi-team manual recovery). Fix direction is **ASYMMETRIC: ALWAYS edit the GitOps overlay to match the live infra name; NEVER rename infra to match the overlay** (H-FORCENEW-DIRECTION-3). Verify the live name first: `az keyvault list` / `az appconfig list`.
- **SQL LTR `immutability_locked = true` is an IRREVERSIBLE WORM lock** — cannot be unlocked/deleted; carries `prevent_destroy`. NEVER offer a `= false` rollback; read `docs/00-mssql-immutability.md` first; validate in `Unlocked` mode before locking (H-IMMUTABLE-3).
- **Removing a `moves.tf` `moved{}` block before the migration applied in ALL envs ⇒ Terraform destroy+recreate** of stateful Cosmos/SQL (H-MOVES-4). Default = KEEP.
- **KV `network_acls` is default-deny + fully declarative (REPLACES, not appends)** — a partial edit locks out all apps (H-KVACL-5). Edit as a strict superset; never hardcode a computed AGW IP; prefer the PE/subnet layer.
- **MC connectivity: whitelist-OFF at task end is MANDATORY (H-FINALLY)** even if the op failed — leaving it on = security violation + CI Terraform drift.
- FTO: NEVER edit `values-override.yaml` (CD-owned, image SHA only) — edit `values.yaml`. `featureBranchEnvironment.enabled:true` ONLY in `values.devmc.yaml`.

## Probe starters
```bash
az account show --query id -o tsv          # must equal the TARGET subscription
az keyvault list -o table ; az appconfig list -o table   # live names before any rename
git -C <repo> grep -n 'immutability_locked\|moved {\|prevent_destroy'
```

## Sibling skills / tools
`eneco-platform-mc-vpp-infra` (read-only `mc-vpp-domain-lookup.sh`, `mc-vpp-module-versions.sh`, `mc-vpp-env-diff.sh`), `eneco-flex-trade-optimizer` (FTO terragrunt), `eneco-pull-request-review-ado` (Terragrunt `dependency` vs `dependencies` DAG review), `eneco-tools-connect-mc-environments` (login/whitelist — see `eneco-clis-and-tools.md`).

## Near-miss (route elsewhere)
- an ArgoCD OutOfSync with no Terraform symptom → `surface-gitops-argocd`.
- an Azure Monitor metric alert (not a plan/apply) → `surface-azure-resource-alert`.
- a Service Bus topic/subscription/DLQ governance question → `surface-messaging-servicebus`.
