# Surface: pipeline-ado

Azure DevOps pipeline / build failures and PR review. Note:
`eneco-pull-request-review-ado` is a `findings` code-review workflow, NOT an
incident kind — it is the HAND-OFF target when "the fix is a PR". Primary siblings:
`eneco-pull-request-review-ado`, `eneco-fbe-troubleshoot` (service-build child pipelines).

## Trigger signals
- ADO pipeline/build failure (stage/task); `NU1902` / `NU1903` (NuGet CVE audit gate, `TreatWarningsAsErrors`); git error on a pipeline (e.g. BtM pipeline `git error`); PAT expiry.
- "review this PR" / "ADO code review" / "security review of PR changes"; dev.azure.com PR URLs; iteration commits.
- Tech in the change: Terraform/Terragrunt, Kubernetes manifests, Go, Python, TypeScript, API-contract changes.

## Orthogonal probe surfaces (do-not-collapse)
- Review hierarchy is bottom-up: **DESIGN → CORRECTNESS → SECURITY → COMPLEXITY → STYLE** (a design flaw invalidates style feedback).
- **Terragrunt `dependency` (singular, output mock) ≠ `dependencies` (plural, run-all DAG edge)** (H-DAG-ORDER-1) — only plural serializes execution; a missing one = non-deterministic `SubnetNotFound` on parallel `run-all` that PASSES a single-module apply. (Directly relevant to FTO/MC Terragrunt incidents.)
- `allow_blob_public_access = true` = BLOCKING by runtime blast radius, not HCL optics (H-BLOB-DEFAULT-1).
- ADO iteration drift: a thread with a bare `rightFileStart` line + no `iterationContext` anchors to the current view → after a push it lands on DIFFERENT code (H-ADO-ITER-1).

## Safety gates
- **`status: review` recipes are recognition-ONLY** — never paste as remediation (H-STATUS-1). A NuGet CVE audit finding is a recognition signal, not a fix to apply.
- ADO PAT needs `Code (Read & Write)` for posting — a 403 only appears at POST time, so front-load the scope check (H-PAT-SCOPE-1).
- The **User Approval Gate (Phase G) is BLOCKING** before posting any review thread; degraded modes (`*-BLOCKED`) REFUSE to post when a required reference is missing — they do not silently post.
- NEVER echo PATs/secrets.

## Probe starters
```bash
az pipelines build show --id <build-id> -o json      # + timeline for the failing stage
# PR review goes through eneco-pull-request-review-ado scripts: ado-pr-fetch/diff/threads/comment.sh
```

## Sibling skills / tools
`eneco-pull-request-review-ado` (Phases A→G; subagents `linus-torvalds`, `uncle-bob`, `el-demoledor`, `socrates-contrarian`, `architect-kernel`; `ado-pr-*.sh`; needs `AZURE_DEVOPS_EXT_PAT`), `eneco-fbe-troubleshoot` (service-build child pipelines, NuGet gate), `eneco-context-repos` (PR browse via `ado-list-prs`, `ado-pr-details`).

## Near-miss (route elsewhere)
- a green build but a runtime URL 404 → `surface-gitops-argocd` (build ≠ runtime health).
- a `terraform apply` failure (not a pipeline-orchestration failure) → `surface-terraform-iac-apply`.
- a deploy that needs MC connectivity → see `eneco-clis-and-tools.md` for the session protocol.
